-Leave her alone! Stop!

07:16.303 --> 07:18.571
♪ A better way,
I'd better wait ♪

07:18.573 --> 07:20.439
Stop! Damn it!

07:20.441 --> 07:22.041
-♪ Gotta find a way ♪
-Stop!

07:22.043 --> 07:23.776
-Damn it!
[ Tires squeal ]

07:23.778 --> 07:25.378
Stop!

07:25.380 --> 07:28.047
[ Grunting ]

07:28.049 --> 07:32.251
♪♪

07:32.253 --> 07:36.189
[ Breathing heavily ]

07:48.135 --> 07:50.570
[ Keys clack ]

07:58.613 --> 08:00.012
[ Keys clack ]

08:00.014 --> 08:01.947
Ohh.

08:01.949 --> 08:04.216
You don't quit, do you?

08:04.218 --> 08:06.419
Sorry.
Did I wake you?

08:06.421 --> 08:07.753
Nope.

08:07.755 --> 08:09.822
What do you think about
setting up a bridge loan

08:09.824 --> 08:11.224
to buy
another building?

08:11.226 --> 08:14.560
Come on. Seriously?
I just woke up.

08:14.562 --> 08:15.961
I'm sorry.

08:15.963 --> 08:17.963
It's just the apartment
buildings aren't selling.

08:17.965 --> 08:20.833
I figured we could use the money
to start another business.

08:20.835 --> 08:23.502
[ Chuckles ]

08:23.504 --> 08:25.838
Oh, you are such
a greedy bastard.

08:25.840 --> 08:27.372
I swear.

08:27.374 --> 08:29.108
Just trying
to keep up momentum.

08:29.110 --> 08:31.777
Um...

08:31.779 --> 08:34.113
well, the loan,
I guess it just --

08:34.115 --> 08:36.048
it just depends on
revenue stream.

08:36.050 --> 08:38.183
Yeah, but we could do a couple
of jobs and figure it out.

08:38.185 --> 08:42.121
Okay, J, I am not
your attorney anymore.

08:43.858 --> 08:45.791
I thought...

08:45.793 --> 08:49.394
I don't know, we were
trying something else.

08:49.396 --> 08:51.797
So, no more advice?

08:51.799 --> 08:54.533
No.
I'm done talking.

08:54.535 --> 09:02.308
♪♪

09:11.152 --> 09:13.552
[ Knock on door ]

09:13.554 --> 09:15.154
Hey.

09:15.156 --> 09:17.356
Hey.

09:17.358 --> 09:20.425
I thought I'd make the deposit
before we open.

09:20.427 --> 09:22.895
Yep.

09:22.897 --> 09:25.298
[ Grunts ]

09:30.037 --> 09:32.705
[ Lock clicking ]

09:34.709 --> 09:36.642
[ Safe door opens ]

09:38.779 --> 09:41.180
Are we gonna deposit
$20,000 this week?

09:41.182 --> 09:43.516
Nah.

09:45.320 --> 09:48.521
I don't want to draw
too much attention at the bank.

09:48.523 --> 09:50.990
Gonna wait till spring break.
We'll be slammed.

09:50.992 --> 09:55.260
We can start jacking up
the prices, start moving more.

09:55.262 --> 09:57.597
Alright?

10:02.537 --> 10:04.070
[ Door opens ]

10:08.075 --> 10:10.009
Hey, what's up, Trey?

10:10.011 --> 10:11.877
Deran.

10:11.879 --> 10:13.145
How you doing?

10:13.147 --> 10:15.814
Oh, you know,
shit runs downhill.

10:15.816 --> 10:16.815
[ Chuckles ]

10:16.817 --> 10:20.085
Sure does.
You want a little top-off there?

10:20.087 --> 10:22.154
Yeah.
Thank you, boss.

10:22.156 --> 10:27.159
I, uh, heard you got paid 10K
by some asshole in Newport Beach

10:27.161 --> 10:29.228
to shape him a balsa gun.

10:29.230 --> 10:33.899
Yeah. Probably get hung on
a wall, never even get wet.

10:33.901 --> 10:35.634
That was a couple of months
back, though.

10:35.636 --> 10:38.371
I haven't shaped anything
worth riding in a while.

10:38.373 --> 10:39.972
Ah, come on.
I doubt that.

10:39.974 --> 10:41.174
[ Cash register opens ]

10:41.176 --> 10:42.841
No, really.
I can't, uh, concentrate.

10:42.843 --> 10:45.444
I got a bunch of assholes
renting a house next to me.

10:45.446 --> 10:49.248
What do you call them?
Uh...influencers.

10:49.250 --> 10:50.515
Jesus.

10:50.517 --> 10:52.251
Two dickhead brothers
from Irvine.

10:52.253 --> 10:56.655
Driving me crazy with their
online party video bullshit.

10:56.657 --> 10:58.391
Oh, that sucks.
I'm sorry to hear that.

10:58.393 --> 10:59.858
Yeah, it's just not right,
you know?

10:59.860 --> 11:01.794
People come from out of town,
they move here,

11:01.796 --> 11:04.863
and just make life shitty
for the rest of us.

11:04.865 --> 11:09.001
♪♪

11:09.003 --> 11:10.803
Yeah.

11:10.805 --> 11:14.207
♪♪

11:14.209 --> 11:16.141
Well, uh, can I
get you anything?

11:16.143 --> 11:17.943
A couple eggs?
Some toast?

11:17.945 --> 11:20.212
No, no, no.
Coffee top-off is just fine.

11:20.214 --> 11:23.348
I just was rolling by,
thought I'd stop by, say hey.

11:23.350 --> 11:26.018
Haven't seen you much
since Smurf died.

11:26.020 --> 11:27.820
Alright.
Take it easy.

11:27.822 --> 11:30.222
Alright, Trey.
Take it easy, buddy.

11:30.224 --> 11:31.757
Take it easy, Tommy.

11:31.759 --> 11:34.359
-See you, Trey.
-See you later.

11:34.361 --> 11:38.431
♪♪

11:38.433 --> 11:40.900
[ Door closes ]

11:42.303 --> 11:43.969
You gonna make that deposit
or what?

11:43.971 --> 11:45.370
Tommy: Yeah.

11:45.372 --> 11:55.114
♪♪

11:55.116 --> 12:04.457
♪♪

12:04.459 --> 12:07.259
You want a sandwich?

12:07.261 --> 12:09.162
Sure.

12:11.132 --> 12:13.432
[ Can tab pops ]

12:14.735 --> 12:19.338
Do you prefer it diagonal
or horizontal?

12:20.541 --> 12:22.808
Whatever, man.
You choose.

12:35.222 --> 12:36.789
Thanks.

12:38.359 --> 12:40.493
What were you doing
this morning?

12:40.495 --> 12:42.395
I was at the lot.

12:44.832 --> 12:48.301
Oh, yeah? You figured out what
you want to do with it yet?

12:48.303 --> 12:50.369
No.

12:51.772 --> 12:53.839
Well, it's --
I guess it's only been

12:53.841 --> 12:56.309
about three months,
right?

12:56.311 --> 12:58.110
So?

12:58.112 --> 13:02.247
So, it's not much use to us
just sitting there.

13:02.249 --> 13:07.320
♪♪

13:07.322 --> 13:10.389
Not everything
is about money, J.

13:10.391 --> 13:13.259
Mm.
No, I know.

13:14.862 --> 13:16.729
But this is.

13:16.731 --> 13:20.132
♪♪

13:20.134 --> 13:22.935
We need to look for
another job, man.

13:22.937 --> 13:26.572
Otherwise, we just keep taking
losses and racking up debt.

13:28.876 --> 13:30.743
What do you think?

13:30.745 --> 13:34.279
I think it's my lot, and I'm
gonna do with it what I want

13:34.281 --> 13:36.281
when I want.

13:36.283 --> 13:40.285
♪♪

13:40.287 --> 13:41.554
Okay.

13:41.556 --> 13:43.222
-J.
-Hmm?

13:43.224 --> 13:47.026
Get square bologna next time
you do the shopping, please.

13:49.964 --> 13:51.564
[ Knife cuts ]

13:51.566 --> 13:54.467
[ Indistinct talking ]

14:03.244 --> 14:04.377
[ Telephone rings ]

14:04.379 --> 14:06.511
Here you are.

14:06.513 --> 14:09.048
Smurf.

14:09.050 --> 14:12.117
Thank you for looking after
them, Detective. Let's go.

14:12.119 --> 14:14.821
We're gonna have to
hang on to Andrew.

14:16.391 --> 14:17.990
Why?

14:17.992 --> 14:20.525
He attacked two people
with his skateboard.

14:20.527 --> 14:21.860
Sent one
to the hospital.

14:21.862 --> 14:24.663
He was protecting himself
and his sister.

14:24.665 --> 14:26.531
The school thinks
they were involved

14:26.533 --> 14:28.868
in the theft
of computers.

14:28.870 --> 14:30.636
They weren't.

14:32.873 --> 14:37.142
This isn't gonna work
if you make us look stupid.

14:37.144 --> 14:39.812
♪♪

14:39.814 --> 14:42.748
Why don't you tell
Lieutenant Mackey

14:42.750 --> 14:44.817
that my attorney will be
in touch tomorrow

14:44.819 --> 14:49.422
to straighten this out,
but I'm taking my kids home.

14:49.424 --> 14:58.498
♪♪

15:01.970 --> 15:03.369
[ Baby crying ]

15:03.371 --> 15:06.104
Did you see that?

15:06.106 --> 15:08.975
Yeah, he just started paddling.
-Oh.

15:08.977 --> 15:11.744
Just held him,
he started paddling.

15:13.381 --> 15:15.982
You know, I think he might be
ready to tandem.

15:15.984 --> 15:17.984
-We'll see.
-What are you talking about?

15:17.986 --> 15:19.852
Arlo took Kai out
at six months.

15:19.854 --> 15:22.054
Arlo's a lunatic.

15:22.056 --> 15:24.857
Well, what do you think
about preschool, bud?

15:24.859 --> 15:27.526
He doesn't need
preschool yet.

15:27.528 --> 15:29.328
Of course he does.

15:29.330 --> 15:30.529
Why?

15:30.531 --> 15:32.398
Well, social shit.
All that stuff.

15:32.400 --> 15:34.533
He's with Enrique's kids
all day.

15:34.535 --> 15:37.336
He's social.

15:37.338 --> 15:40.606
Look, how much longer
are your cousins gonna
keep babysitting us?

15:40.608 --> 15:42.008
I don't know.

15:42.010 --> 15:45.011
It's been months,
Renn.

15:45.013 --> 15:47.813
What, you just never
gonna trust me again?

15:47.815 --> 15:54.152
♪♪

15:54.154 --> 15:57.155
-Que pasa?
-Hay una problema.

15:57.157 --> 15:59.758
Nunca lo consiguio.

15:59.760 --> 16:03.495
Mijo. Mira me.
Mira me.

16:03.497 --> 16:05.631
Mira me, mijo.

16:05.633 --> 16:09.235
He's good.
Strong.

16:09.237 --> 16:11.838
What are you benching?
250?

16:11.840 --> 16:14.240
-What's going on?
-I gotta go to work.

16:14.242 --> 16:16.775
-Wait, already?
-Craig.

16:16.777 --> 16:18.911
-You can't just
leave him with me?
-No, I can't, Craig.

16:18.913 --> 16:20.979
You know the deal.
-Come on.

16:20.981 --> 16:22.514
Craig.

16:22.516 --> 16:28.054
♪♪

16:28.056 --> 16:31.924
[ Baby fussing ]

16:33.461 --> 16:34.993
I'll call you.

16:34.995 --> 16:41.667
♪♪

16:41.669 --> 16:47.806
♪♪

16:47.808 --> 16:52.278
I appreciate the ambition, Baz,
but your plan was stupid.

16:52.280 --> 16:55.013
Why?
We got away with it.

16:55.015 --> 16:58.284
You do realize that computers
have serial numbers, right?

16:58.286 --> 16:59.752
Yeah, so?

16:59.754 --> 17:02.821
So, what's the point in stealing
something you can't fence?

17:02.823 --> 17:06.358
Hey, you?

17:06.360 --> 17:09.095
You just forgot about
SAT prep or what?

17:09.097 --> 17:11.297
You scout for these two?

17:11.299 --> 17:14.833
[ Man speaking indistinctly
on TV ]

17:14.835 --> 17:19.237
You realize that I have to
pull every string that I've got

17:19.239 --> 17:21.173
to keep Andrew
out of juvie.

17:21.175 --> 17:22.508
Andrew: Craig!

17:22.510 --> 17:25.844
I never wanted to do this
in the first place.

17:25.846 --> 17:28.246
I like school.

17:28.248 --> 17:30.249
Are you blaming Baz?

17:30.251 --> 17:32.118
'Cause no one
forced you.

17:32.120 --> 17:35.321
Seriously? Like both of you
wouldn't have given me shit
if I bailed?

17:35.323 --> 17:37.256
Now I'm gonna get expelled
from school.

17:37.258 --> 17:42.661
Hey, look, Smurf will talk
to the principal, right?

17:42.663 --> 17:44.730
Yeah.

17:44.732 --> 17:50.202
♪♪

17:50.204 --> 17:53.005
I'll take care of it.

17:54.675 --> 17:56.475
I doubt it.

17:56.477 --> 17:59.678
Ms. Zane is more honest
than your cops.

17:59.680 --> 18:02.214
You guys
are unbelievable.

18:02.216 --> 18:06.552
♪♪

18:06.554 --> 18:08.487
Hormones.

18:08.489 --> 18:11.023
[ Talking continues ]

18:11.025 --> 18:13.826
[ Refrigerator door opens ]
So...

18:13.828 --> 18:20.098
how do you feel about pot roast
for dinner to celebrate?

18:20.100 --> 18:21.900
[ Refrigerator door closes ]

18:21.902 --> 18:23.902
Celebrate what?

18:23.904 --> 18:26.505
Me stealing a bunch
of worthless shit?

18:26.507 --> 18:28.007
No.

18:29.577 --> 18:31.644
Come here.

18:31.646 --> 18:38.784
♪♪

18:38.786 --> 18:41.454
It's our anniversary.

18:43.057 --> 18:47.125
Six years ago...

18:47.127 --> 18:48.594
today.

18:50.731 --> 18:54.133
You walked in
that door...

18:56.004 --> 19:01.740
...and I knew
I had another son.

19:01.742 --> 19:10.949
♪♪

19:10.951 --> 19:12.418
Here.

19:13.554 --> 19:15.487
To you.
[ Glass clinks ]

19:15.489 --> 19:20.826
♪♪

19:20.828 --> 19:24.162
[ Exhaling sharply ]

19:24.164 --> 19:27.499
[ Heavy metal music playing ]

19:27.501 --> 19:30.136
[ Exhales sharply ]

19:32.640 --> 19:34.707
[ Exhales sharply ]

19:34.709 --> 19:40.579
♪♪

19:40.581 --> 19:46.318
♪♪

19:46.320 --> 19:48.587
Hey, man, what's up?

19:48.589 --> 19:50.789
Hey, what are you doing here,
man?

19:50.791 --> 19:53.325
Just thought I'd come by
and check it out.

19:53.327 --> 19:55.261
What's that's mural
gonna be?

19:55.263 --> 19:57.497
That's gonna be
the ambiance.

19:58.666 --> 20:02.268
Just paid my guy 5K.
It's gonna be sick.

20:02.270 --> 20:04.470
Did you get an invoice?

20:04.472 --> 20:06.538
Yeah, for 10 grand.

20:06.540 --> 20:07.606
Good.

20:07.608 --> 20:09.875
What about a sign
out front?

20:09.877 --> 20:12.278
Help pull people in
from the street.

20:12.280 --> 20:14.280
Why would I
want to do that?

20:14.282 --> 20:17.149
Well, you gotta have
as many people coming
through here as possible.

20:17.151 --> 20:18.951
I got a legit list
of 40 names.

20:18.953 --> 20:21.754
Driver's licenses, addresses,
social security numbers.

20:21.756 --> 20:23.756
I mean,
gym memberships

20:23.758 --> 20:25.958
are already
at half capacity on the books.

20:25.960 --> 20:27.760
Where'd you get
the names?

20:27.762 --> 20:29.695
From the Giving Tree, man.
Why? What's it matter?

20:29.697 --> 20:32.498
-I'm just saying, if anyone --
-Look, man, I got it covered.

20:32.500 --> 20:35.568
Alright? I don't need you coming
here and checking in on me.

20:35.570 --> 20:38.236
You got it?

20:38.238 --> 20:40.639
Got it.

20:40.641 --> 20:42.508
Good job.

20:42.510 --> 20:46.512
♪♪

20:46.514 --> 20:48.848
Here you go, boss.

20:50.518 --> 20:54.253
Hey, can you cut it
with the whole "boss" shit?

20:54.255 --> 20:56.989
-Yeah. No problem.
-Just...

20:56.991 --> 20:58.791
Thank you.

20:58.793 --> 21:00.192
Tommy.

21:00.194 --> 21:02.261
[ Bottles rattle ]

21:02.263 --> 21:04.330
Did you --
you have Trey come by

21:04.332 --> 21:06.732
and tell me about this
influencer shit?

21:06.734 --> 21:10.669
No.
I didn't have to.

21:10.671 --> 21:14.072
People are talking,
you know?

21:14.074 --> 21:16.875
What are they
talking about?

21:16.877 --> 21:19.211
Just...

21:19.213 --> 21:21.413
I mean, if you and your brothers
aren't gonna handle shit

21:21.415 --> 21:24.150
like that, who is?

21:24.152 --> 21:26.152
You know?

21:28.156 --> 21:30.889
[ Sniffs ]

21:30.891 --> 21:34.292
[ Telephone ringing ]

21:34.294 --> 21:41.367
♪♪

21:41.369 --> 21:43.301
Yeah?

21:43.303 --> 21:45.771
<i> That Pope?</i>
<i> It's Gia.</i>

21:47.307 --> 21:48.975
What do you want?

21:48.977 --> 21:51.177
<i> Can we talk?</i>

21:54.314 --> 21:56.983
[ Telephone beeps ]

21:56.985 --> 21:58.584
Who was that?

21:58.586 --> 22:00.052
Gia.

22:00.054 --> 22:01.587
Said she wants to talk.

22:04.324 --> 22:08.060
Jesus.
I have not been here in ages.

22:08.062 --> 22:10.262
What do you want?

22:10.264 --> 22:12.532
Well,
hello to you, too.

22:14.869 --> 22:17.069
I've got something for you.
A job.

22:17.071 --> 22:18.937
So, you don't trust us enough
to fence our shit,

22:18.939 --> 22:22.408
but you want us
to pull a job for you?

22:22.410 --> 22:24.610
Look, I hear things.
You guys are doing okay.

22:24.612 --> 22:27.079
-[ Scoffs ]
-Staying out of trouble.

22:27.081 --> 22:29.948
So, if this goes well,

22:29.950 --> 22:33.285
I'm willing to discuss renewing
our previous relationships.

22:33.287 --> 22:35.321
What's the job?

22:36.691 --> 22:38.691
I need you
to clear a warehouse.

22:38.693 --> 22:40.559
Of what?

22:40.561 --> 22:42.361
There's a new chick
in town.

22:42.363 --> 22:44.430
Thinks she's hot shit because
she can tell the difference

22:44.432 --> 22:46.232
between a Byzantine
and a Roman coin.

22:46.234 --> 22:48.234
Right.
So, you've got competition.

22:48.236 --> 22:49.635
Hardly.

22:49.637 --> 22:52.438
She's an amateur who fell
into some good pieces.

22:52.440 --> 22:54.040
Not that she knows
what to do with them.

22:54.042 --> 22:55.574
And you do?

22:55.576 --> 22:57.743
Got a buyer
all lined up.

23:02.383 --> 23:04.182
We'll think about it.

23:04.184 --> 23:08.120
♪♪

23:08.122 --> 23:09.922
Okay.

23:11.059 --> 23:13.992
Don't think too long.

23:13.994 --> 23:15.828
Gentlemen.

23:17.732 --> 23:19.665
You really thinking
about working with her

23:19.667 --> 23:21.701
after what she did
to us?

23:23.003 --> 23:24.202
[ Car door closes ]

23:24.204 --> 23:26.138
It's a job.

23:26.140 --> 23:29.275
♪♪

23:38.152 --> 23:41.654
♪ How does it feel? ♪

23:44.158 --> 23:48.160
♪ How does it feel? ♪

23:48.162 --> 23:50.429
Gia: Shit. You know what?
I-I need to go.

23:50.431 --> 23:52.831
I'll call you back.

23:52.833 --> 23:55.001
So?

23:56.037 --> 23:58.637
Yeah,
we're interested.

23:58.639 --> 24:00.773
Great.

24:00.775 --> 24:03.709
All you need.

24:03.711 --> 24:08.181
♪♪

24:08.183 --> 24:10.216
There a problem?

24:12.387 --> 24:16.556
Are you still angry
about how we left things?

24:17.592 --> 24:20.326
You gotta learn
how to let shit go.

24:22.063 --> 24:24.529
Are the plans in here?

24:24.531 --> 24:26.265
Yeah.

24:26.267 --> 24:28.333
What about security?

24:28.335 --> 24:30.069
ADT.
Same as me.

24:30.071 --> 24:32.071
You know
the response time?

24:32.073 --> 24:34.673
Seven minutes.
Max.

24:34.675 --> 24:37.276
Okay.

24:39.614 --> 24:41.947
Alright.
We'll be in touch.

24:41.949 --> 24:44.584
[ Footsteps depart ]

24:46.020 --> 24:49.222
Private seller.
You like them?
[ Door opens ]

24:49.224 --> 24:52.558
Gia, I love them.
[ Door closes ]

24:54.495 --> 24:57.896
But I just don't have the cash
on hand right now.

24:57.898 --> 24:59.398
Mm.

25:01.235 --> 25:03.702
How about a trade?

25:03.704 --> 25:05.838
What do you have?

25:05.840 --> 25:07.506
Computers.

25:07.508 --> 25:10.042
They're perfectly good...

25:10.044 --> 25:12.311
as long as no one wants
to use the warranty.

25:12.313 --> 25:15.047
Smurf, what am I gonna do
with those?

25:15.049 --> 25:17.450
You'll figure it out.

25:17.452 --> 25:20.853
♪♪

25:20.855 --> 25:22.588
Fine.

25:22.590 --> 25:23.922
For you.

25:23.924 --> 25:25.925
Gia, Gia, Gia.

25:25.927 --> 25:29.462
♪♪

25:29.464 --> 25:31.764
Julia's
really grown up.

25:33.268 --> 25:36.102
[ Exhales sharply ]
Remember 16?

25:37.472 --> 25:39.138
I do.

25:39.140 --> 25:42.041
[ Chuckles ]
Good luck.

25:43.611 --> 25:46.011
[ Laughs ]

25:46.013 --> 25:47.947
Yeah.

25:47.949 --> 25:51.550
Why didn't you come help me
pull up the tiles at the bar?

25:51.552 --> 25:53.952
Trying to avoid bars
right now.

25:53.954 --> 25:56.555
Oh. Yeah. Still doing
the sober thing, huh?

25:56.557 --> 25:58.157
Still doing
the sober thing.

25:58.159 --> 26:00.893
I know it's really hard
for you to get.
-Right.

26:00.895 --> 26:03.963
I just don't understand why
you can't come and help me out

26:03.965 --> 26:05.898
and not have a drink.

26:05.900 --> 26:08.167
[ Grunts ]

26:08.169 --> 26:10.435
Only see one camera.

26:10.437 --> 26:13.639
Yeah, J said
there's armed security.

26:13.641 --> 26:17.109
It's got ADT, seven-minute
response time.

26:17.111 --> 26:19.644
Probably got sensors on all
the windows and doors, too.

26:19.646 --> 26:21.646
Why don't we just go in
through the roof?

26:21.648 --> 26:23.382
Nah.
We're in plain sight here, man.

26:23.384 --> 26:25.584
There's a lot of people.
There's a lot of foot traffic.

26:25.586 --> 26:27.252
Yeah, well, let's go
a couple of buildings over

26:27.254 --> 26:28.854
and just head over
from there.

26:28.856 --> 26:31.056
They probably got sensors
on top of the roof, too.

26:31.058 --> 26:32.925
We can't just drill through
the top of it.

26:32.927 --> 26:35.394
It's gonna create
a shitload of noise.

26:35.396 --> 26:36.996
Man, it's only gonna take
a couple of minutes.

26:36.998 --> 26:38.397
We just get something
to cover the sound.

26:38.399 --> 26:40.733
It's not
that big a deal.

26:40.735 --> 26:41.934
Maybe.

26:41.936 --> 26:43.669
Definitely.

26:44.939 --> 26:46.672
Great.

26:46.674 --> 26:51.344
♪♪

26:59.887 --> 27:07.760
♪♪

27:07.762 --> 27:10.863
Look, uh, hey, see
if she starts now.

27:13.168 --> 27:15.634
A-And, uh, let her run
for a while,

27:15.636 --> 27:17.370
and make sure
she's not running hot.

27:17.372 --> 27:18.904
-Alright.
-Yeah.

27:18.906 --> 27:20.706
Hey, you still mad?

27:20.708 --> 27:22.441
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
[ Engine starts ]

27:22.443 --> 27:24.910
Come on. Why don't you
have a beer with me?

27:24.912 --> 27:27.780
You know?
Think about something else, hmm?

27:27.782 --> 27:29.382
[ Clears throat ]

27:29.384 --> 27:31.316
Hey. Hey, Gia.
How you doing?

27:31.318 --> 27:32.918
Baz. Julia.

27:32.920 --> 27:35.921
I need you to take the computers
to this address.

27:35.923 --> 27:38.523
And next time,
save Smurf the grief, okay?

27:38.525 --> 27:40.859
Think jewelry.

27:40.861 --> 27:44.463
♪♪

27:44.465 --> 27:45.998
[ Engine idling ]

27:46.000 --> 27:49.468
Going through the roof's
gonna be harder than we thought.

27:49.470 --> 27:52.405
-Why?
-They retrofitted it
three years ago.

27:52.407 --> 27:54.073
Steel plating and beams
throughout.

27:54.075 --> 27:56.642
Well, then we just use
the plasma cutters.

27:57.745 --> 28:00.546
That would probably
set the roof on fire.

28:01.749 --> 28:03.883
I think I know
what to do.

28:03.885 --> 28:06.018
-Hmm?
-It's gonna be loud, though.

28:06.020 --> 28:07.552
Well, how loud?

28:07.554 --> 28:11.290
You know,
like gunshots loud.

28:11.292 --> 28:14.293
Okay.
I can figure that out.

28:14.295 --> 28:16.295
I'll get to work.

28:16.297 --> 28:26.305
♪♪

28:26.307 --> 28:36.315
♪♪

28:36.317 --> 28:43.188
♪♪

28:43.190 --> 28:46.191
♪ Los paranois ♪

28:46.193 --> 28:49.194
♪ Come to destroy us ♪

28:49.196 --> 28:52.665
♪ Los paranois ♪

28:52.667 --> 28:54.133
Yeah!

28:54.135 --> 28:56.469
What's up, Carcinogens?!

28:56.471 --> 28:59.272
It's your boy, Carson!
God, I missed you!

28:59.274 --> 29:02.341
What's up, bro?
What's up? Yeah!

29:02.343 --> 29:04.877
God, look at this.
You kidding me?

29:04.879 --> 29:07.480
You guys ready to play?
I know I am.

29:07.482 --> 29:09.414
Are you guys ready to play?!
-Yeah, boy!

29:09.416 --> 29:11.150
Yeah! Let's go!
Come on!

29:11.152 --> 29:13.486
Pump it up!
Yeah!

29:13.488 --> 29:16.622
Who are these beautiful
Oceanside girls

29:16.624 --> 29:18.223
we got here tonight?

29:18.225 --> 29:20.625
Oh, my gosh.
What a pick tonight.

29:20.627 --> 29:22.962
Ooh. Mm.
Hi. Hi. Hi.

29:22.964 --> 29:24.897
You.

29:24.899 --> 29:26.365
Get in here.

29:26.367 --> 29:29.168
♪ Make me say, "Ooh" ♪

29:29.170 --> 29:31.236
♪ Ooh ♪

29:31.238 --> 29:33.038
Alright, alright.
What do we think, guys?

29:33.040 --> 29:36.175
How many tries is it gonna take
Ashley here to get a mouthful?

29:36.177 --> 29:38.511
[ Inhales sharply ]
I don't know. Let's find out.

29:38.513 --> 29:41.314
Come on. Come on.
Everybody, cheer her on.

29:41.316 --> 29:45.050
Let's go!
Yeah, Ashley, Ashley.

29:45.052 --> 29:47.653
Whoo!

29:47.655 --> 29:49.522
Go, girl, get in there.
-Oh, get in there.

29:49.524 --> 29:51.590
Don't be afraid.

29:51.592 --> 29:53.192
[ All cheering ]

29:53.194 --> 29:55.995
Oh, first try!
What?!

29:55.997 --> 29:58.463
Damn, you wanted to get
in there with me, huh?

29:58.465 --> 30:01.667
Hey, we love our fans.
Make sure to check out
the merch, hit us up

30:01.669 --> 30:04.069
on Patreon,
all that good stuff.

30:04.071 --> 30:05.804
You know the drill.

30:05.806 --> 30:07.673
Oh, snap!

30:07.675 --> 30:10.009
You guys, we got us
another local in the house

30:10.011 --> 30:13.412
trying to get in on these
sweet carcinogenic vibes, right?

30:13.414 --> 30:15.681
What's up, brother?

30:15.683 --> 30:19.284
You guys are too loud.
You gotta wrap this shit up.

30:19.286 --> 30:21.620
Pfft!

30:21.622 --> 30:23.889
[ Australian accent ]
Witness the Oceanside boomer.

30:23.891 --> 30:26.091
He's younger than
the usual boomer

30:26.093 --> 30:29.161
but often just as lame
and boomer-y.

30:29.163 --> 30:30.563
[ Laughs ]

30:30.565 --> 30:32.497
[ Normal voice ] I'm just
playing, bro. It's all good.

30:32.499 --> 30:34.499
We'll keep it down.

30:34.501 --> 30:36.235
Go.
Get the hell out of here.

30:36.237 --> 30:37.636
♪ Make me say, "Ooh" ♪

30:37.638 --> 30:38.837
♪ Ooh ♪

30:38.839 --> 30:40.773
-Ashley, come on.
-What?

30:40.775 --> 30:43.242
-Ashley, get up.
-What?

30:43.244 --> 30:44.443
Hey, hey, hey, babe.

30:44.445 --> 30:45.978
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
we're not done yet.

30:45.980 --> 30:47.446
Where are you going?
We're not done yet.

30:47.448 --> 30:49.314
What?
-Man, just let this go.

30:49.316 --> 30:50.649
Everybody out.

30:50.651 --> 30:54.119
What -- [ Scoffs ]
What is this shit?

30:54.121 --> 30:55.654
Guys!

30:55.656 --> 30:59.324
Hey, Carcinogens, you wanna see
an O-side ass-kicking?

30:59.326 --> 31:01.060
Whoo! Come on!

31:01.062 --> 31:02.995
Come off that.
You kidding me, dude?

31:02.997 --> 31:05.598
Yo, bro, I don't know
what your problem is.

31:05.600 --> 31:07.834
[ Grunts ]

31:09.604 --> 31:11.204
Yo, hey -- Okay.
Hey.

31:11.206 --> 31:14.273
You guys gotta take this
bullshit somewhere else,
alright?

31:14.275 --> 31:17.076
If I see either of you
in Oceanside again,

31:17.078 --> 31:20.345
we're gonna have
some real issues, alright?

31:20.347 --> 31:26.551
♪♪

31:26.553 --> 31:32.958
♪♪

31:32.960 --> 31:35.528
[ Engine starts ]

31:36.697 --> 31:38.563
[ Gear shifts ]

31:38.565 --> 31:47.640
♪♪

31:51.446 --> 32:01.186
♪♪

32:01.188 --> 32:10.929
♪♪

32:10.931 --> 32:20.273
♪♪

32:20.275 --> 32:30.015
♪♪

32:30.017 --> 32:39.558
♪♪

32:39.560 --> 32:49.101
♪♪

32:49.103 --> 32:58.844
♪♪

32:58.846 --> 33:07.786
♪♪

33:07.788 --> 33:10.523
[ Fireworks popping ]

33:10.525 --> 33:20.265
♪♪

33:20.267 --> 33:30.009
♪♪

33:30.011 --> 33:34.413
♪♪

33:34.415 --> 33:35.548
[ Alarm chirps ]

33:35.550 --> 33:38.751
[ Siren wails ]

33:40.154 --> 33:42.021
Pope: [ Grunts ]

33:42.023 --> 33:46.559
[ Siren wails ]

33:46.561 --> 33:56.301
♪♪

33:56.303 --> 34:05.644
♪♪

34:05.646 --> 34:15.388
♪♪

34:15.390 --> 34:25.130
♪♪

34:25.132 --> 34:26.865
You got it?

34:26.867 --> 34:29.134
[ Alarm blaring ]

34:29.136 --> 34:31.604
-You all good?
-Seven minutes.

34:31.606 --> 34:33.538
Let's go.

34:33.540 --> 34:36.275
[ Blaring continues ]

34:36.277 --> 34:46.018
♪♪

34:46.020 --> 34:55.560
♪♪

34:55.562 --> 35:02.435
♪♪

35:02.437 --> 35:03.636
[ Lighter clicks ]

35:03.638 --> 35:13.846
♪♪

35:13.848 --> 35:15.448
Go!

35:15.450 --> 35:17.250
[ Explosion ]

35:17.252 --> 35:25.658
♪♪

35:25.660 --> 35:27.660
[ Blaring continues ]

35:27.662 --> 35:29.662
[ Glass shatters ]

35:29.664 --> 35:32.798
♪♪

35:32.800 --> 35:35.534
Mrs. Cody, have you considered
sending Andrew

35:35.536 --> 35:38.471
to a school that's better suited
for his disposition?

35:38.473 --> 35:41.641
Maybe one with
a good ROTC program?

35:43.210 --> 35:46.211
Are you saying
that he's done here?

35:46.213 --> 35:48.047
Yes.

35:53.488 --> 35:55.154
And what about Julia?

35:55.156 --> 35:58.157
I think what happened here
over the weekend

35:58.159 --> 36:00.960
is a symptom
of a larger problem with Julia.

36:02.830 --> 36:05.430
-And that's?
-She's not being challenged.

36:05.432 --> 36:09.035
It's like something
is holding her back.

36:11.172 --> 36:13.906
Now, I think with
a little encouragement

36:13.908 --> 36:16.041
and more rigorous
class schedule,

36:16.043 --> 36:18.978
Julia could really begin to
start fulfilling her potential,

36:18.980 --> 36:21.514
with the support
of all of us here

36:21.516 --> 36:24.016
and you at home.

36:26.253 --> 36:29.388
[ Siren wailing,
police radio chatter ]

36:29.390 --> 36:31.590
Man: Ready to go!

36:31.592 --> 36:34.527
[ Indistinct conversations ]

36:34.529 --> 36:37.262
[ Police radio chatter ]

36:37.264 --> 36:40.265
Woman: He said
extend the perimeter.

36:40.267 --> 36:44.269
[ Chatter, conversations
continue ]

36:44.271 --> 36:47.139
I worked with your mother
for 30 years.

36:47.141 --> 36:48.741
We were like family.

36:48.743 --> 36:51.076
You abandoned us
as soon as she died.

36:51.078 --> 36:53.145
She never would have
let you do this.

36:53.147 --> 36:56.048
[ Exhales sharply ]
Smurf would have done worse.

36:57.151 --> 37:00.219
It was
a business decision.

37:00.221 --> 37:03.822
She would tell you
never burn bridges.

37:03.824 --> 37:07.026
My clients aren't gonna be
happy about this,

37:07.028 --> 37:09.162
so you should
watch your ass,

37:09.164 --> 37:11.430
'cause I know you think
you're the shit,

37:11.432 --> 37:13.699
but there is always
someone bigger.

37:13.701 --> 37:15.768
Are you done?

37:17.238 --> 37:19.705
Insurance will pay for
the buildings and the rugs.

37:19.707 --> 37:25.310
The rest is your penance for
not being loyal to our family.

37:25.312 --> 37:30.383
<i> You</i> burned the bridges,
not us.

37:30.385 --> 37:39.759
♪♪

37:44.899 --> 37:46.699
♪ My life is insignificant
enough to never live it ♪

37:46.701 --> 37:48.301
♪ I like to hide behind a screen
because I'm better hidden ♪

37:48.303 --> 37:52.638
Miniature toy soldiers
go for 325 bucks.

37:52.640 --> 37:54.773
♪ Presented
like an exhibition ♪

37:54.775 --> 37:56.441
[ Inhales sharply ]
♪ This is a stream
of consciousness ♪

37:56.443 --> 37:57.910
♪ Without the buffering ♪

37:57.912 --> 38:00.179
♪ No need to syndicate,
I'm on demand and lovin' it ♪

38:00.181 --> 38:02.247
That's like $1,000 a shot,
you know?

38:02.249 --> 38:04.383
♪ My virtual reality is
all I need to feel like
everything is meaningful ♪

38:04.385 --> 38:07.186
-Yo, take this out of my cut.
-Yeah, whatever.

38:07.188 --> 38:09.322
We should put it all
in a safe.

38:09.324 --> 38:12.391
-That's a good idea.
-How much did they say
this one was?

38:12.393 --> 38:14.994
[ Cellphone buzzing ]
Mm.

38:14.996 --> 38:17.062
Five grand.
-Five grand?

38:17.064 --> 38:18.797
It's ugly.
-Hey.

38:18.799 --> 38:20.799
♪ It's like my head
is in the cloud right now ♪

38:20.801 --> 38:23.536
We all just need
to slow down.

38:23.538 --> 38:26.005
You got a light?

38:26.007 --> 38:28.473
-Look at this guy.
-What?

38:28.475 --> 38:30.142
When did you start
smoking weed?

38:30.144 --> 38:31.610
[ Lighter clicks ]

38:31.612 --> 38:33.879
Look at this guy.

38:33.881 --> 38:36.281
[ Inhales sharply ] Since I
got back from the desert.

38:36.283 --> 38:40.886
♪ Can't connect to anything
but my phone ♪

38:40.888 --> 38:45.024
♪ Who put you in charge
to bring me back up? ♪

38:45.026 --> 38:46.959
I'm gonna get my cigarettes.

38:46.961 --> 38:48.761
Alright.

38:48.763 --> 38:50.896
How did Gia take it?

38:50.898 --> 38:53.366
She understood.

38:54.369 --> 38:57.570
Nah.
No, I've had enough, man.

38:57.572 --> 39:00.406
'Cause of your mom?

39:02.177 --> 39:06.111
No. 'Cause I got some work
to do later.

39:06.113 --> 39:09.982
♪♪

39:09.984 --> 39:15.454
You know, your mom would have
loved what we did tonight.

39:15.456 --> 39:17.456
She hated Gia.

39:17.458 --> 39:19.025
Really? Why?

39:21.062 --> 39:24.129
Too much like Smurf.

39:24.131 --> 39:26.065
That's a good reason.

39:26.067 --> 39:29.068
That's a very good reason.

39:29.070 --> 39:32.004
Renn. Renn,
I'm telling you --

39:32.006 --> 39:34.073
Renn?

39:34.075 --> 39:36.275
Goddamn it.
This is bullshit.

39:36.277 --> 39:38.477
What happened?

39:38.479 --> 39:40.680
She just canceled on me
again this week.

39:42.083 --> 39:44.149
[ Sighs ]
It's a week.

39:44.151 --> 39:45.618
You'll be fine.
Relax.

39:45.620 --> 39:48.553
Yeah, man, but it's another week
that I don't get to see him.

39:48.555 --> 39:49.822
The kid's an infant.

39:49.824 --> 39:52.691
He's not gonna remember
shit all anyway.

39:52.693 --> 39:55.628
And why the hell
would I listen to you?

39:55.630 --> 39:59.498
In fact, it's 'cause of you
that I can't see my Goddamn kid

39:59.500 --> 40:01.700
unless Renn decides
that it's okay.

40:01.702 --> 40:03.769
[ Sighs ]

40:03.771 --> 40:06.505
What are you
talking about?

40:06.507 --> 40:09.842
That we should have taken him
when I said we should.

40:09.844 --> 40:11.844
You hear me?

40:11.846 --> 40:14.379
What is this about?
Is this about the kid, even?

40:14.381 --> 40:16.782
Huh?

40:16.784 --> 40:20.786
Or this is about the fact that
Renn's got you by the balls?

40:20.788 --> 40:22.521
[ Scoffs ]

40:22.523 --> 40:25.124
Whipped like
a little bitch.

40:25.126 --> 40:34.667
♪♪

40:34.669 --> 40:38.004
[ Water splashes ]

40:48.683 --> 40:51.016
What are you doing?

40:51.018 --> 40:52.818
It's hot.

40:52.820 --> 40:54.419
Yeah?

40:54.421 --> 40:55.888
You should come in.

40:55.890 --> 40:58.223
I'll get my suit.

40:58.225 --> 41:00.359
Ah, just come in.

41:00.361 --> 41:02.627
It's no big deal.

41:02.629 --> 41:05.564
Come on.
I've seen you naked before.

41:05.566 --> 41:14.907
♪♪

41:14.909 --> 41:24.650
♪♪

41:24.652 --> 41:26.919
♪♪

41:26.921 --> 41:29.054
[ Laughs ]

41:29.056 --> 41:31.023
Stop!

41:33.127 --> 41:35.995
[ Water splashes ]
[ Laughs ]

41:35.997 --> 41:39.332
[ Both laughing ]

41:39.334 --> 41:41.800
Baz: [ Gags,
speaks indistinctly ]

41:41.802 --> 41:44.069
[ Laughs ]

41:44.071 --> 41:45.804
No.

41:45.806 --> 41:50.209
♪♪

41:50.211 --> 41:52.611
[ Laughing ] Yeah.

41:52.613 --> 41:54.747
Stop!

41:54.749 --> 41:56.882
Agh!

41:56.884 --> 41:59.685
Oh, my God!

41:59.687 --> 42:05.090
♪♪

42:05.092 --> 42:07.527
Smurf:
[ Opens bottle ]

42:09.230 --> 42:11.964
Julia:
[ Laughing ] No! No!

42:11.966 --> 42:14.734
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

42:17.171 --> 42:19.605
[ Laughs ]

42:21.508 --> 42:24.043
[ Water splashes ]

42:24.045 --> 42:26.045
[ Chuckles ]

42:26.047 --> 42:31.316
♪♪

42:31.318 --> 42:33.619
Julia!

42:35.456 --> 42:40.693
You should put some clothes on
around your brothers.

42:42.730 --> 42:44.263
You wanna join?

42:44.265 --> 42:48.000
♪♪

42:48.002 --> 42:49.735
[ Sits glass down ]

42:52.073 --> 42:54.207
Ooh. [ Chuckles ]

42:54.209 --> 42:58.277
♪♪

42:58.279 --> 43:01.848
You look like
a little drowned rat.

43:04.551 --> 43:07.486
Why don't you go inside
and dry off?

43:07.488 --> 43:10.222
It's okay.
I have my shirt.

43:10.224 --> 43:16.629
♪♪

43:16.631 --> 43:22.501
♪♪

43:22.503 --> 43:25.638
You know, I went
to your school today.

43:25.640 --> 43:27.706
Yeah?

43:27.708 --> 43:29.775
Yeah.

43:29.777 --> 43:32.711
I spoke to
your vice principal.

43:32.713 --> 43:34.647
And?

43:34.649 --> 43:40.853
♪♪

43:40.855 --> 43:47.192
♪♪

43:47.194 --> 43:48.928
You're getting expelled.

43:48.930 --> 43:50.729
What?

43:50.731 --> 43:56.469
I mean, I-I, uh -- I tried
to change her mind.

43:56.471 --> 43:59.538
There just wasn't anything
I could do.

43:59.540 --> 44:01.474
Where are we
gonna go to school?

44:01.476 --> 44:03.408
We'll figure it out.

44:03.410 --> 44:08.213
♪♪

44:08.215 --> 44:10.816
Don't stay up too late.

44:10.818 --> 44:16.955
♪♪

44:16.957 --> 44:18.891
Good night, Andrew.

44:18.893 --> 44:27.099
♪♪

44:27.101 --> 44:29.969
-I'm going to bed.
-Oh, hey, Julia, Julia.

44:29.971 --> 44:32.171
Baz, stop.

44:32.173 --> 44:40.846
♪♪

44:40.848 --> 44:49.188
♪♪

44:49.190 --> 44:50.523
[ Sets glass down ]

44:50.525 --> 44:54.059
[ Breathes deeply ]

44:54.061 --> 44:56.128
[ Water running ]

44:56.130 --> 45:05.871
♪♪

45:05.873 --> 45:14.479
♪♪

45:14.481 --> 45:16.081
[ Water stops ]

45:16.083 --> 45:25.824
♪♪

45:25.826 --> 45:35.168
♪♪

45:35.170 --> 45:44.910
♪♪

45:44.912 --> 45:54.453
♪♪

45:54.455 --> 46:01.294
♪♪

